{"title_page": "Robert Vre\u010der", "text_new": "{{short description|Slovenian racing cyclist}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Robert Vre\u010der\n| image         = Robert Vre\u010der.png\n| image_size    =\n| caption       = Vre\u010der at the 2011 [[Tour of Slovenia]]\n| fullname      = Robert Vre\u010der\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1980|10|8}}\n| birth_place   = [[Celje]], [[Slovenia]]\n| height        = {{convert|1.82|m|abbr=on}}\n| weight        = {{convert|68|kg|abbr=on}}\n| currentteam   = Retired\n| discipline    = Road\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     = All-rounder\n| amateuryears1 =\n| amateurteam1  =\n| proyears1     = 2006\u20132008\n| proteam1      = {{ct|LGS|2006}}\n| proyears2     = 2009\n| proteam2      = {{ct|ADR|2009}}\n| proyears3     = 2010\n| proteam3      = {{ct|PER|2010}}\n| proyears4     = 2011\n| proteam4      = Obrazi Delo Revije\n| proyears5     = 2012\n| proteam5      = {{ct|VBG|2012}}\n| proyears6     = 2013\n| proteam6      = {{ct|EUS|2013}}\n| proyears7     = 2014\n| proteam7      = {{ct|VBG|2014}}\n| majorwins     =\n}}\n'''Robert Vre\u010der''' (born 8 October 1980) is a [[Slovenia]]n former professional [[road racing cyclist]], who rode professionally between 2006 and 2014 for the {{ct|LGS|2008}}, {{ct|ADR|2009}}, {{ct|PER|2010}}, {{ct|EUS|2013}},<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/african-number-one-among-new-euskaltel-signings|title=African number one among new Euskaltel signings|work=[[Cyclingnews.com]]|publisher=[[Future plc]]|location=[[Bath, Somerset|Bath]], [[England]]|date=22 October 2013|accessdate=1 September 2014|author=Peter Cossins}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://road.cc/content/forum/67036-transfers-2013-world-and-pro-continental-tours|title=Transfers for 2013 (World and Pro Continental Tours)|work=road.cc|publisher=Farrelly Atkinson Ltd|location=[[Bath, Somerset|Bath]], [[England]]|date=20 September 2013|accessdate=1 September 2014|author=}}</ref> and {{ct|VBG|2014|nolink=yes}} teams.<ref name=\"proteam\">{{cite news|url=http://www.euskalteleuskadi.com/es/equipo-ciclista/robert-vrecer.html|title=Robert Vre\u010der at Euskaltel-Euskadi|date=28 December 2012|accessdate=7 March 2013|work={{ct|EUS|2013}}|publisher=|location=[[Bilbao]], [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque Country]]}}</ref><ref name=\"gr\">{{cite news|url=http://www1.skysports.com/cycling/news/22854/8860492/cycling-transfers-team-by-team-guide-to-which-riders-are-on-the-move-and-where|title=Cycling transfers: Team-by-team guide to which riders are on the move and where|work=[[Sky Sports]]|publisher=[[BSkyB]]|location=[[London]], [[England]]|date=31 December 2013|accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"VBG\">{{cite news|url=http://www.radsport-news.com/sport/sportnews_84968.htm|title=Vrecer kehrt zum Team Vorarlberg zur\u00fcck|language=German|trans-title=Vrecer returns to Team Vorarlberg|work=Radsport-News|publisher=Sport Aktiv Media GmbH|location=[[Rodgau]], [[Hesse]]|date=25 November 2013|accessdate=24 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nFollowing a positive [[clomifene]] control,<ref name=\"doper\">{{cite news|url=http://www.slovenskenovice.si/sport/drugi-sporti/dopingirani-vrecer-molci|title=Dopingirani Vre\u010der mol\u010di|language=Slovenian|trans-title=Vre\u010der Doped|work=[[Slovenske Novice]]|author=Marko Ur\u0161i\u010d|publisher=[[Delo (company)|Delo]]|location=[[Ljubljana]], [[Slovenia]]|date=10 April 2014|accessdate=1 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"cheater\">{{cite news|url=http://06.live-radsport.ch/details_191690/DopingNews_Verfahren_gegen_Robert_Vrecer_eroumlffnet__positiver_Test_bei_PolenRundfahrt_2013.html|title=Doping-News: Verfahren gegen Robert Vrecer er\u00f6ffnet - positiver Test bei Polen-Rundfahrt 2013|language=German|trans-title=Doping News: proceedings against Robert Vrecer opened - positive test at Tour of Poland 2013|work=Radsport-News|author=Felix Griep|publisher=Sport Aktiv Media GmbH|location=[[Rodgau]], [[Hesse]]|date=9 April 2013|accessdate=1 September 2014}}</ref> Vre\u010der was suspended, for twenty months, on 30 July 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uci.ch/mm/Document/News/CleanSport/16/57/75/Antidopingruleviolation2014_Neutral.PDF|title=List of Dopers and Suspensions|accessdate=2 September 2014|work=[[UCI World Tour]]|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|location=[[Aigle]], [[Vaud]]}}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n'''Sources:'''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=25703|title=Robert Vre\u010der at Cycling Archives|date=28 December 2012|accessdate=7 March 2013|work=Cycling Archives|publisher=|location=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingbase.com/Robert-Vrecer.html|title=Robert Vre\u010der at Cycling Base|date=28 December 2012|accessdate=6 January 2013|work=Cycling Base|publisher=|location=}}</ref>\n{{Div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;2008\n:9th [[Trofeo Zs\u0161di]]\n;2009\n:2nd [[GP Kranj]]\n:10th [[Trofeo Zs\u0161di]]\n;2010\n:1st [[File:Jersey yellow.svg|20px]] Overall [[Istrian Spring Trophy]]\n::1st Prologue & Stage 2\n:1st [[File:Jersey yellow.svg|20px]] Overall [[Tour de Slovaquie]]\n::1st Stages 4 & 5\n:8th [[Trofeo Zs\u0161di]]\n;2011\n:1st [[File:Jersey yellow.svg|20px]] Overall [[Szlakiem Grod\u00f3w Piastowskich]]\n:1st [[File:Jersey yellow.svg|20px]] Overall [[Istrian Spring Trophy]]\n::1st Prologue & Stage 2\n: National Road Championships\n::2nd [[Slovenian National Time Trial Championships|Time trial]]\n::7th [[Slovenian National Road Race Championships|Road race]]\n:3rd Overall [[Tour of Slovenia]]\n::1st Prologue\n;2012\n: National Road Championships\n::1st [[File:MaillotEslovenia.PNG|20px]] [[Slovenian National Time Trial Championships|Time trial]]\n::7th [[Slovenian National Road Race Championships|Road race]]\n:1st [[File:Jersey yellow.svg|20px]] Overall [[Tour of Greece]]\n::1st Stage 1\n:2nd [[Gran Premio Nobili Rubinetterie]]\n:3rd Overall [[2012 Tour of Austria|Tour of Austria]]\n: