years6     = 2013\n| proteam6      = {{ct|EUS|2013}}\n| proyears7     = 2014\n| proteam7      = {{ct|VBG|2014}}\n| majorwins     =\n}}\n'''Robert Vre\u010der''' (born 8 October 1980) is a retired [[Slovenia]]n professional [[road racing cyclist]]. He rode professionally between 2006 and 2014. After seven seasons competing domestically with the [[Radenska (cycling team)|Radenska-Powerbar]], {{ct|ADR|2009}}, {{ct|PER|2010}}, Obrazi Delo Revije, and {{ct|VBG|2012}} squads,<ref name=\"proteam\">{{cite news|url=http://www.euskalteleuskadi.com/es/equipo-ciclista/robert-vrecer.html|title=Robert Vre\u010der at Euskaltel-Euskadi|date=28 December 2012|accessdate=7 March 2013|work={{ct|EUS|2013}}|publisher=|location=[[Bilbao]], [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque Country]]}}</ref> Vre\u010der signed with {{ct|EUS|2013}}, a [[UCI ProTeam]], for the 2013 season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/african-number-one-among-new-euskaltel-signings|title=African number one among new Euskaltel signings|work=[[Cyclingnews.com]]|publisher=[[Future plc]]|location=[[Bath, Somerset|Bath]], [[England]]|date=22 October 2013|accessdate=1 September 2014|author=Peter Cossins}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://road.cc/content/forum/67036-transfers-2013-world-and-pro-continental-tours|title=Transfers for 2013 (World and Pro Continental Tours)|work=road.cc|publisher=Farrelly Atkinson Ltd|location=[[Bath, Somerset|Bath]], [[England]]|date=20 September 2013|accessdate=1 September 2014|author=}}</ref>  Vre\u010der rejoined {{ct|VBG|2014|nolink=yes}} for the 2014 season, after his previous team&nbsp;\u2013 {{ct|EUS|2013|nolink=yes}}&nbsp;\u2013 folded.<ref name=\"gr\">{{cite news|url=http://www1.skysports.com/cycling/news/22854/8860492/cycling-transfers-team-by-team-guide-to-which-riders-are-on-the-move-and-where|title=Cycling transfers: Team-by-team guide to which riders are on the move and where|work=[[Sky Sports]]|publisher=[[BSkyB]]|location=[[London]], [[England]]|date=31 December 2013|accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"VBG\">{{cite news|url=http://www.radsport-news.com/sport/sportnews_84968.htm|title=Vrecer kehrt zum Team Vorarlberg zur\u00fcck|language=German|trans-title=Vrecer returns to Team Vorarlberg|work=Radsport-News|publisher=Sport Aktiv Media GmbH|location=[[Rodgau]], [[Hesse]]|date=25 November 2013|accessdate=24 December 2013}}</ref> Following a positive [[clomifene]] control,<ref name=\"doper\">{{cite news|url=http://www.slovenskenovice.si/sport/drugi-sporti/dopingirani-vrecer-molci|title=Dopingirani Vre\u010der mol\u010di|language=Slovenian|trans-title=Vre\u010der Doped|work=[[Slovenske Novice]]|author=Marko Ur\u0161i\u010d|publisher=[[Delo (company)|Delo]]|location=[[Ljubljana]], [[Slovenia]]|date=10 April 2014|accessdate=1 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"cheater\">{{cite news|url=http://06.live-radsport.ch/details_191690/DopingNews_Verfahren_gegen_Robert_Vrecer_eroumlffnet__positiver_Test_bei_PolenRundfahrt_2013.html|title=Doping-News: Verfahren gegen Robert Vrecer er\u00f6ffnet - positiver Test bei Polen-Rundfahrt 2013|language=German|trans-title=Doping News: proceedings against Robert Vrecer opened - positive test at Tour of Poland 2013|work=Radsport-News|author=Felix Griep|publisher=Sport Aktiv Media GmbH|location=[[Rodgau]], [[Hesse]]|date=9 April 2013|accessdate=1 September 2014}}</ref> Vre\u010der was suspended, for twenty months, on 30 July 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uci.ch/mm/Document/News/CleanSport/16/57/75/Antidopingruleviolation2014_Neutral.PDF|title=List of Dopers and Suspensions|accessdate=2 September 2014|work=[[UCI World Tour]]|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|location=[[Aigle]], [[Vaud]]}}</ref>\n\n==Palmar\u00e8s==\n'''Sources:'''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=25703|title=Robert Vre\u010der at Cycling Archives|date=28 December 2012|accessdate=7 March 2013|work=Cycling Archives|publisher=|location=}}</ref><ref>{{cite n